subject:

RENEWED CLARITY (12-15-20)
===================================================================
verse:

Now we see things imperfectly as in a poor
mirror, but
then we will see everything with perfect clarity. All that
I know now is partial and incomplete, but
then I will
know everything completely, just
as God knows me now.
(I Cor.13:12)

===================================================================
reflection:

Paul offers a glimpse into the future to
give us hope that
one day we will be complete when we see God face to
face. This truth should strengthen
our faith. We don’t
have all the answers now, but one day we will. Someday
we
will see Christ in person and be able to see with
God’s perspective.

===================================================================
prayer:

Lord, thank You for the hope that one day we will see You face to face and be made complete in Your presence. Strengthen our faith when answers are unclear, and anchor our hearts in the promise of Your perfect wisdom. Teach us to trust Your timing and walk by faith until the day we see with Your perspective. Amen.

===================================================================
